In this press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs comments on a variety of topics. He discusses the potential release of an American hiker in Iran and the ongoing focus on the economy. He also addresses the controversy surrounding the planned burning of the Quran by a Florida pastor, emphasizing the potential danger it poses to American troops and the negative impact on US-Islamic relations. Additionally, Gibbs mentions the consideration of reaching out to the pastor directly to discourage the burning and confirms that the FBI is involved in assessing the situation. The briefing concludes with questions about tax cuts, the proposed mosque near Ground Zero, and the President's plans for the defense authorization bill.